Right now you can't create your own instances of ConfluenceHomeLogAppender to log to your own log file, because the switchAppender() method, which needs to be called to properly initialise the ConfluenceHomeLogAppender, is package protected. We should either make this method public, or even better create an appender specifically for use by plugins which are loaded after the bootstrapping is done anyway, and therefore don't need event based initialisation.

